
#string concatenation (how to put strings together)

plural1=input("plural noun: ")
plural2=input("plural noun:")
verb=input("verb: ")
noun1=input("noun: ")
ing_verb=input("verb: ")
plural3=input("plural noun: ")
noun2=input("noun2: ")
plural4=input("plural noun: ")

at_the_arcade= f"When I go to the arcade with my {plural1} there are lots of games to play. I spend lots of time there with my friends. In the game X-Men " \
               f"you can be different {plural2}. The point of the game is to {verb} every robot. You also need to save people. Then you can go to the next level." \
               f"In the game Star Wars you are Luke Skywalker and you try to destroy every {noun1}. " \
               f"In a car racing/motorcycle racing game you need to beat every computerized vehicle that you are {ing_verb} against." \
               f"There are a whole lot of other cool games. When you play some games you win {plural3} for certain scores. " \
               f"Once you're done you can cash in your tickets to get a big {noun2}. " \
               f"You can save your {plural4}for another time. " \
               f"When I went to this arcade I didn't believe how much fun it would be. " \
               f"So far I have had a lot of fun every time I've been to this great arcade!"
print(at_the_arcade)
